text: Danane (, ) is a coastal town in the southern Lower Shebelle province of Somalia. It is located approximately to the southwest of the nation's capital Mogadishu. == History == In the past the Italians set a concentration camp in the town for people that resisted the Italian colonial leaders in Ethiopia. Many Ethiopians were detained in Danane. == Demographics == Danane is the traditional territory and primarily inhabited Bimal clan == References == Category:Populated places in Lower Shebelle
title: Danane
